<t>CREATE TABLE FitnessData ( 
 id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
 user_id INT, 
 workout_type VARCHAR(50), 
 workout_duration INT, 
 calories_burned INT 
);</t><s>UPDATE FitnessData SET workout_type='Cardio', workout_duration=60, calories_burned=300 WHERE id=1;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  duration INTERVAL
);

CREATE TABLE exercises (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  muscle_group VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE fitness_logs (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_id UUID REFERENCES workouts(id),
  exercise_id UUID REFERENCES exercises(id),
  date DATE NOT NULL,
  sets INT,
  reps INT
);</t><s>UPDATE users SET age = age + 1 WHERE id = '123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  duration INTERVAL
);

CREATE TABLE exercises (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  muscle_group VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE fitness_logs (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),

  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_id UUID REFERENCES workouts(id),
  exercise_id UUID REFERENCES exercises(id),
  date DATE NOT NULL,
  sets INT,
  reps INT
);

CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT
);</t><s>UPDATE users SET age = age + 1 WHERE id = '123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000';</s>

  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_id UUID REFERENCES workouts(id),

  date DATE NOT NULL,
  sets INT,

<t>CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

<t>CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);</t><s>update users set age = age + 1 where user_id = '123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000';</s>

    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);</t><s>UPDATE activities SET difficulty_level = 3 WHERE activity_id = 1;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>UPDATE activities SET difficulty_level = 3 WHERE activity_id = 1;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>update activities set difficulty_level = 3 where activity_id = 1;</s>

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);</t><s>UPDATE activities SET difficulty_level = 3 WHERE activity_id = 1;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>UPDATE goals SET completed = TRUE WHERE goal_id = 1;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>update goals set completed = true where goal_id = 1;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)

    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

);

    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,

    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
